evidence: In this study, we attempted to apply a similar strategy (metastability-engineering) in TiZrHfV x Nb x Ta x (x = 1.0, 0.5, and 0.1) RHEAs (hereafter referred to as VNTx) for the further development of high strength and ductile TRIP RHEAs.

The mechanical properties and deformation behavior of the present RHEAs were investigated by uniaxial compression tests at room temperature. Fig.  3 (a) presents the compressive true strainstress curves of the as-cast VNTx (x = 1.0, 0.5, and 0.1) RHEAs. The yield strength enhanced with an increase of V, Nb, and Ta contents (0.5 and 1.0 at. percentages). Moreover, VNT1.0 and VNT0.5 RHEAs show excellent room temperature plasticity with less strain-hardening behavior, compared to VNT0.1.

In present work, the TiZrHfV x Nb x Ta x (x = 1.0, 0.5, and 0.1) RHEAs have been designed and developed by applying the metastabilityengineering alloy design strategy  [9, 11] . The V, Nb, and Ta were selected as the additional elements into TiZrHf alloy to enhance the strength and plasticity through the solid-solution strengthening effect (which mainly stems from lattice distortion), work hardening effect, and stress/strain-induced phase transformation.
